I upgraded from Fvwm 2.2.2 to 2.4.2 and 2.4.3. Now, when I move any window
over a Netscape window, Netscape redraws the exposed areas with a dark grey

background.

For example,

 1. Bring up Netscape 4.76 (Solaris build).
 2. View a page with a white background.
 3. Bring up any other window. An easy choice is to use Alt-F to bring up
    the Find dialog.
 4. Drag the Find window over the Netscape window.
 5. Chunks of the Netscape window background will appear in dark gray.

I tried turning on BackingStore and SaveUnder and saw no change. Other
windows don't seem to have this problem.

I run in 24-bit color mode.

Relevant(?) .fvwm2rc file entries:

Style *			SloppyFocus
Style *			StickyIcon, MinOverlapPercentPlacement
Style *			NoIcon, NoPPosition, DecorateTransient
Style *			BorderWidth 4, HandleWidth 4
Style *			MWMDecor, MWMFunctions
Style *			ResizeOpaque
Style *			BackingStore
Style *			SaveUnder
Style "Netscape"	MiniIcon netscape.t.pm

I'd like to blame this on Netscape, but the problem didn't appear with
Fvwm 2.2.2. I just tried Fvwm 95 and it also doesn't appear there.



