> Please try opaque move from time to time, it is one command, you know. :)

I tested it some last night. It's somewhat jerky; then again, MultiPixmap
doesn't fair much worse than TiledPixmap in that respect. But I think plugging
Fvwm into, say, Imlib2 would go very contrary to the developers' style ;-)

> I mean instead of 6 ordered pixmaps to have named parameters like:
>   Main decor/title-main.xpm, TextUnder decor/title-textunder.xpm, ...

Ah, that's a good idea. Seems more user-friendly and extensible than the
position-dependent syntax.

The leftmain/rightmain/leftbutton/rightbutton extensions should be pretty
easy to add on this way...of course, the user won't need to specify them
unless they care.

Suzanne

