Regarding the FvwmIconMan module, it would be useful for those of us that
are addicted to AutoRaise functionality if there was the ability to raise &
warp to a window after the mouse hovers on an entry in the icon manager for
a specified number of milliseconds.

I had something like this in mind - just kind of a general auto-event after
hovering over an entry in the icon manager for a while :

FvwmIconMan*auto   trueFvwmIconMan*autodelay  1000
FvwmIconMan*autowarp  false
FvwmIconMan*autodeiconify  true
FvwmIconMan*autoraise  true

That would raise and deiconify it (if needed) after the delay, but it
wouldn't warp the mouse there.  I don't think that there's anything else
that you'd want to do to a window after hovering on it in the icon manager
- I thought of the ability to pass FvwmIconMan an Fvwm function
handle/pointer, but I don't even know if that's possible.




