On 10 Oct 2001 03:16:09 -0400, Suzanne Britton wrote:
> 
> Here's the latest incarnation of the spiffy titlebars patch. It's not yet
> guaranteed stable or in its final form, but it's getting there. This one was
> generated against 2.4.3. It fixes a silly crashing bug and changes to a new
> position-independent format for the MultiPixmap TitleStyle.
> 
> There are ten pixmaps, all of which are optional except for Main (or, define
> both LeftMain and RightMain):
> 
> Main                      - tiled all the way across before anything else
> LeftMain, RightMain       - tiled on the left and right sides of the title
>                             (if titleless and no Main, LeftMain is tiled all
>                             the way across)
> UnderText                 - tiled underneath the title text
> LeftButtons, RightButtons - tiled underneath left and right buttons in case of
>                             ButtonStyle -- UseTitleStyle
>                             (if not specified, LeftMain/RightMain is used, if
>                              that isn't specified, Main is used)
> LeftEnd, RightEnd         - Non-tiled pixmaps for the far ends of the titlebar
>                             (just before the buttons)
> LeftOfText, RightOfText   - Non-tiled pixmaps for left and right ends of text
> 
> This may sound daunting, but there's very little overhead for a decor if
> TitleStyle MultiPixmap isn't used (and 0 overhead if #undef FANCY_TITLEBARS,
> of course). Just a single unallocated Picture** pointer.

Is anyone against applying this/updated patch? It is #ifdef'd and does not
add any memory overhead or instability when the new feature is not used.

Suzanne, it seems logical to have Buttons pixmap, not only LeftButtons and
RightButtons. Or I may add this later myself.

There is one bug with stippled titles, try opaque move of sticky windows.
The stipples disappear when they should be redrawn during the move.
To be honest I don't know what to do with stipples when MultiPixmap used.
Stipples don't look very nice with MultiPixmap or TiledPixmap titlebars.

Regards,
Mikhael.
