After upgrading from Fvwm 2.4.0 to 2.4.3, some of my keybindings stopped
working. After a bit of testing I found that I needed to use KP_Left
instead of KP_4 etc. in the below:

Key KP_4	A	M	Scroll -100 +0
Key KP_Left	A	M	Scroll -100 +0
<snip>

I cannot make these work with Shift+Control at all, however if I exchange
Shift for Meta they work:

Key KP_4	A	SC	CursorMove -1 0
Key KP_Left	A	SC	CursorMove -1 0
Key KP_6	A	SC	CursorMove +1 +0
Key KP_Right	A	SC	CursorMove +1 +0
<snip>

I have Control+<numpad key> bound to other actions, which now happens
regardless if I have Shift pressed or not, so it seems Shift is here
ignored, or something like that.

While with Shift+Meta, it worked as before; I did not need to use KP_Left
etc.:

Key KP_4	A	SM	CursorMove -10 +0
Key KP_6	A	SM	CursorMove +10 +0
<snip>

My old keybindings worked fine with Fvwm 2.4.3 on Solaris 2.7.


