> If I look in ~/.gnome-errors, I find:
> 
> [FVWM][ParseBinding]: <<ERROR>> No such key: Help

The binding for the Help key (if you have one) is built into FVWM.
We recently added this warning for key bindings that don't match
any key.  I think the message is useful for debugging but
is going to cause more problems than its worth.

If there are no objections, I'll disable the warning.

> I think this must be something Accelerated X doesn't support or something.
> This happens before my .fvwm2rc file is loaded.
> 
> [FVWM][GetWindowSizeHints]: <<WARNING>> XMMS window 0x400001a has broken (max
> _width) size hints
> Please report this to fvwm-workers@fvwm.org

This warning helps find applications that set invalid hints
but sending the report to us always generates the same response from
us, Ie., notify the application owner.

I think its time to change the message to "please notify the
owner of the application".

Any objection to this change?

