Greets!

Behold the latest fancy-titlebar patch. I've cleaned up the code a little,
added in a "Buttons" pixmap option (for tiling under the buttons in
UseTitleStyle if LeftButtons/RightButtons isn't defined), added the
ability to stretch pixmaps instead of tiling, and took a stab at documenting
this mess in fvwm2.1.

You can now put a "stretched" flag after a pixmap name, like this:

   TitleStyle MultiPixmap Main (stretched) foo.xpm, UnderText bar.xpm

Now the Main pixmap will be scaled, but UnderText will be tiled as usual.
Note that this flag will only affect Main, LeftMain, RightMain, and UnderText.

The primary drawback with stretching is that it can't (yet) be extended very
well with UseTitleStyle. This would be somewhat tricky since the buttons are
rendered separately from the rest of the titlebar. Instead, whatever pixmap is
rendered under the buttons will always be tiled (even if it were stretched, it
wouldn't necessarily be seamless because it would start anew with each
button). It may be best not to use UseTitleStyle at all in this case and just
build the background you want into the buttons--this is the way most themes
(IceWM, Sawfish, etc.) are distributed anyways.

It'd be nice if someone could figure out a way to stretch a pixmap *all* the
way across the titlebar, including under buttons, but it's a task to which I am
not up :-)

The patch is now about 19k and, on my system, adds 2368 bytes to the stripped
executable when FANCY_TITLEBARS is #defined :-) It seems to be reasonably
complete and stable, but due to continued absence of our new back-ordered
monitor, I haven't been able to test it extensively yet (it's not that X won't
come up...it just *hurts* to look at!)

Suzanne

