I though that I dealt with this situation and I actually got reports that
Restart without parameters works on a dual head setup like yours.

The trick is that when you use Restart on some screen, "-s" is added to the
end of all original arguments of fvwm2. This trick was used in the earlier
fvwm versions too, but it was too buggy regarding different Restart cases.
Currently this switch is added once just after forking for each screen.

I don't know why it does not work for you. Can you create ~/bin/fvwm2
wrapper that looks like:

  #!/bin/sh
  echo "[fvwm2 on $DISPLAY called with args]: $@"
  /usr/local/bin/fvwm2 "$@"

and use "Restart --pass-args ~/bin/fvwm2" command to see what parameters
are passed to fvwm2 on one or another screen, and send the output?

BTW, you may use this slightly modified wrapper and this Restart command
if you want to add additional parameters. But this should not be needed,
since a simple Restart without parameters should work.

Regards,
Mikhael.
