in fvwm/add_window.c, Bool setup_window_placement(..),

If XGetCommand() returns client_argc of 0 and client_argv of NULL ptr,
trying to do client_argv[0] in following function calls, such as
MergeCmdLineResources, GetResourceString, etc., will cause core dump.

I am not even close to being an experienced X programmer so I don't know if
it's a normal behavior for XGetCommand to return null ptr, but it makes
sense to me.  I worked around it for my own use by enclosing a whole set of
stuff in:

  if (client_argc) {...}
I doubt that's the correct way to fix it.  I looked at 2.4.0 code (because
it didn't coredump like 2.4.3) and I see it's completely changed.

I was running dinotrace when fvwm2 crashed.  It is 100% reproducible.
I'm sorry to have bothered you if this is already known (I browsed through
bug tracking list and didn't find anything similar) or if I'm way off
somewhere such as it being an XF86 bug and not fvwm bug.



